29/05/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- On Wednesday (28 May), the BiH presidency re-affirmed its support for a bilateral agreement with the United States that exempts US citizens from prosecution by the International Criminal Court. The immunity agreement was sealed on 16 May and now waits for ratification by parliament, despite pressure from the EU not to sign it.
In other news, High Representative Paddy Ashdown announced the creation of a Bulldozer Committee for Agriculture, during a visit to Prijedor on Wednesday. Talking to local farmers, Ashdown noted the potential in BiH for mass production of healthy food, if the business environment is improved. (OHR Sources - 29/05/93; PBS BiH, Onasa, RTRS - 28/05/03)
